Random image partitions

Distance dependent Chinese Restaurant Process (ddCRP) linking probablity

From our GSI 2013 paper:

\[ p(\boldsymbol{c}_{i} = j | D,f,\alpha) \propto \begin{cases} f(d_{ij}) & j \neq i \\ \alpha & j = i \end{cases} \]

Sample one random partition from the prior

ddCRP <- function(i, D, alpha) {
    di = D[i, ]
    di[i] = alpha
    linkIndex = rmultinom(1, 1, di)
    cj = which(linkIndex == 1)
    return(cj)
}

sampleLinks <- function(X, D, alpha) {
    N = dim(X)[2]
    links = matrix(0, 1, N)
    for (i in 1:dim(links)[2]) {
        links[i] = ddCRP(i, D, alpha)
    }
    return(links)
}

Posterior inference with Gibbs sampling

Input data

computeMAP <- function(V, X, Gamma, variance, W = 0) {
    if (length(W) == 1) {
        W = matrix(1, 1, noOfVoxels)
    }

    d = dim(V)[1]
    N = dim(V)[2]
    # X[1:d,] = t(scale(t(X[1:d,]),center=TRUE,scale=FALSE))

    Phi = matrix(0, 0, d * (d + 1) * dim(W)[1])
    for (i in 1:N) {
        Phi = rbind(Phi, t(W[, i]) %x% t(X[, i]) %x% diag(1, 2))
    }

    GammaCheck = 1/variance * t(Phi) %*% Phi + Gamma
    logmap = solve(GammaCheck) %*% (1/variance * t(Phi) %*% c(V))

    return(logmap)
}

computeMarginalLikelihoodFixedLowercaseSigma <- function(V, X, Gamma, variance, 
    W = 0) {
    if (length(W) == 1) {
        W = matrix(1, 1, noOfVoxels)
    }

    d = dim(V)[1]
    N = dim(V)[2]
    # X[1:d,] = t(scale(t(X[1:d,]),center=TRUE,scale=FALSE))

    Phi = matrix(0, 0, d * (d + 1) * dim(W)[1])
    for (i in 1:N) {
        Phi = rbind(Phi, t(W[, i]) %x% t(X[, i]) %x% diag(1, 2))
    }

    GammaCheck = 1/variance * t(Phi) %*% Phi + Gamma
    normalizingConstant = 1/2 * log(det(variance * Gamma)) - d * N/2 * log(2 * 
        pi * variance) - 1/2 * log(det(variance * GammaCheck))
    marginalLikeihood = normalizingConstant + 1/(2 * variance) * t(c(V)) %*% 
        Phi %*% solve(variance * GammaCheck) %*% t(Phi) %*% c(V)

    return(marginalLikeihood)
}

Sampling

\[ p(\boldsymbol{c}_{i} | \boldsymbol{c}_{i-1}, \boldsymbol{v}, \mu,\Gamma,\sigma_{v}^{2}, D,f,\alpha) \propto \begin{cases} p(\boldsymbol{c}_{i}|D,f,\alpha) B(\boldsymbol{v},z(\boldsymbol{c}),\mu,\Gamma,\sigma_{v}^{2}) & \text{if } \boldsymbol{c}_{i} \text{ joins } k \text{ and } l \\ p(\boldsymbol{c}_{i}|D,f,\alpha) & \text{otherwise, } \end{cases} \]

# compute joint marginal likelihood
computeJointMarginal <- function(partitions, V, X, Gamma, variance) {
    jointMarginal = 0
    for (j in 1:max(partitions)) {
        Xj = as.matrix(X[, which(partitions == j)])
        Vj = as.matrix(V[, which(partitions == j)])
        jointMarginal = jointMarginal + computeMarginalLikelihoodFixedLowercaseSigma(Vj, 
            Xj, Gamma, variance)
    }
    return(jointMarginal)
}

# sample posterior link given data for one pixel
posterior_ddCRP <- function(i, links, partitions, D, alpha, V, X, Gamma, variance) {
    # posterior_ddCRP <- function(i,links,partitions,D,alpha,V,X,K,n0,S0) {

    # compute BF, remove link
    links[i] = i
    partitions = createPartition(links)
    oldMarginal = computeJointMarginal(partitions, V, X, Gamma, variance)

    di = D[i, ]
    indices = which(di > 0)
    for (j in indices) {

        # new link
        links[i] = j
        partitions = createPartition(links)
        newMarginal = computeJointMarginal(partitions, V, X, Gamma, variance)

        bayesFactor = exp(newMarginal - oldMarginal)

        if (!is.finite(bayesFactor)) {
            di[j] = (.Machine$double.xmax - alpha)/length(di)
        } else {
            di[j] = bayesFactor
        }

    }

    di[i] = alpha
    # print(paste('di=',di))
    linkIndex = rmultinom(1, 1, di)
    cj = which(linkIndex == 1)

    result = list(cj = cj, di = di)
    return(result)
}

# one step in the Gibbs sampler: visiting all pixels once
gibbsStep <- function(step, links, partitions, D, alpha, V, X, Gamma, variance) {
    # gibbsStep <- function(step,links,partitions,D,alpha,V,X,K,n0,S0) {

        results = posterior_ddCRP(i, links, partitions, D, alpha, V, X, Gamma, 
            variance)
        links[i] = results$cj
        # links[i] = posterior_ddCRP(i,links,partitions,D,alpha,V,X,K,n0,S0)
        partitions = createPartition(links)

        # matrix(logmap,dimension,dimension+1) mapMatrix =

Gamma = B %x% diag(1, dimension)
